    <article class="art-hed">
        <h3><a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2019/12/the-tragedy-of-the-toilets-lifestyle">The tragedy of the toilets</a></h3>
                    </article>

                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>As queer, trans, Black and Brown communities mourn, we must resist letting our pain and suffering be instrumentalized by those who seek to justify Islamophobia and war. Our pain and trauma are not for them&mdash;neither are our joy, rage, suffering, struggle and resilience. We must continue to tell other, truer stories. They are darker and more intricate but, ultimately, infinitely more beautiful.  </p>
<p class="MsoNormal"></p>
<p><em style="background-color: initial;">Bennett Carpenter is a graduate student in the literature department.</em></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><!--EndFragment--></p>
